<CENTER><H1>ISSUES</H1>

<h2>Drugs</h2>
<hr>

</center>
Emppower America Brochure:<a href="/empower/drug-surge.html">Reclaiming the War on Drugs,</a> October 1996.
<P>
<a href="/empower/drug-drugs.html">Statement by William J. Bennett</a> on Results of National Household Survey on Drug Abuse, August 20, 1996.
<p>
<a href="/empower/drug-drugiss.html">Issue Briefing</a>, "Drugs in America"
<p>
<a href="/empower/drug-drugtest.html">Written Testimony</a> by William J. Bennett, delivered before U.S. Senate Caucus on International Narcotics Control, April 25, 1996
<p>
<a href="/empower/ps-12125.html">A 1996 View of the Drug Problem in America,</a> Statement on release of a Gallup Poll, by William Bennett, December 12, 1995.
<P>
<a href="/empower/aedrugs.html">"Drugs, the Clinton Administration and the Abdication of Responsibility"</a>, testimony by William J. Bennett, delivered before the Senate Judiciary Committee, February 10, 1995.
<p>
<a href="/empower/columbia.html">Columbia, America's Favorite `Narco-Democracy'</a>, by William J. Bennett, <I>Wall Street Journal</I>, April 4, 1995.
<p>
<a href="/empower/suddenly.html">Suddenly Losing the War Against Drugs</a>, by William J. Bennett and John P. Walters, <I>Washington Times</I>, February 7, 1995.
<p>
<a href="/empower/record.html">A Record of Failure in Drug Treatment</a>, by William J. Bennett and John P. Walters, <I>Washington Times</I>, February 8, 1995.
<p>
<a href="/empower/whyaren.html">Why Aren't We Attacking the Supply of Drugs? </a>, by William J. Bennett and John P. Walters, <I>Washington Times</I>, February 9, 1995.
<p>
<a href="/empower/losing.html">Losing the Drug War Without a Fight</a>, by William J. Bennett, <I>Washington Times</I>, February 10, 1995.
<p>
<a href="/empower/renewing.html">Renewing the War on Drugs</a>, by William J. Bennett and John P. Walters, <i>Washinton Times</i>, Febuary 10,1995.
<p>
<a href="/empower/2drugs.html">Drugs section</a> from <I>Empower America's 1996 Candidate School Briefing Book.</I>
