<h2>Jane Fortson</h2>
<p><img src="fortson.gif" align="left" hspace="10">
Forston comes to the Foundation with an extensive background in finance
               and urban development. A Managing Director at Lewis, deRozario Inc.,
               she served as senior investment banker to numerous municipal and
               mortgage related clients underwriting in excess of $2 billion in securities.
               Fortson was appointed by former Mayor Andrew Young as
               commissioner of the Atlanta Housing Authority. She is a founding
               Director of the Atlanta Neighborhood Development Partnership and
               served in the founding Secretariat for the Carter Centers initiative, the
               Atlanta Project.


