<head>
<title>Biography:</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<img src="discussi.gif">
<hr>
<blockquote>
<p>
<font face="arial">
<h2>John Gage, Ph.D.</h2>
<p>

John Gage, Ph.D., is Director of the Science Office of the Sun
Microsystems Computer Corporation. Along with Bill Joy, the Chief
Technical Officer of Sun, Dr. Gage is responsible for Sun's
relationships with the world scientific and public policy
communitites, international scientific institutions and groups
developing new forms of scientific research involving computing.

<p>
<img src="gage.gif" align=right hspace=5 vspace=5>

<p>

Dr. Gage is on the scientific and advisory panels of the United States
National Science Foundaiton, the U.S. Congress Office of Technology
Assessment, the European Institute of Technology, and the United
States National Academy of Sciences.  Dr Gage serves on the Board of
Directors of Unicode, an industry consortium of IBM, Microsoft, Apple,
Novell, Sun, GO Corporation and others to provide multilingual
capability in all world scripts for all documents and applications. In
addition, he has recently been appointed to the U.S. National Research
Council Mathematical Sciences Education Board.

<p>

Educated at the Harvard Business School and the Harvard Graduate
School of Public Policy, Dr. Gage has also done doctoral work in
economics and mathematics at the University of Berkeley.  Dr. Gage
then left Berkeley with Bill Joy to start Sun Microsystems in 1982.

<p>

Dr. Gage is presently an active member of ACM, IEEE, SIAM, AMS, and
SMPTE.

