<blockquote>
<p>
<font face="arial">
<h2>Rich Karlgaard</h2> 
<p>




Rich Karlgaard is the editor of Forbes ASAP, a magazine 
covering the major developments, trends and implications of 
the Information Age. Owned by Forbes, Inc., ASAP is 
delivered six times a year to all 760,000 Forbes magazine 
subscribers.
<p>
<img src="karlgaar.gif" align=right hspace=5 vspace=5>
<p>

Karlgaard joined Forbes in 1992 to help Forbes CEO, 
Malcolm S. Forbes, Jr., and writer George Gilder launch 
ASAP. 
<p>
Regular contributors include Gilder, who is writing 
his next book, Telecosm, serially in the pages of Forbes 
ASAP, and management guru Tom Peters. Other contributors 
include Peter Drucker, Michael Rothschild, Virginia Postrel,
Richard Rapaport, Robert X. Cringely, Alice LaPlante, Andy 
Kessler and Glenn Rifkin.
<p>
Before starting ASAP, Karlgaard co-founded and 
edited Upside magazine, a monthly covering the computer 
industry and high-tech investment. Karlgaard also co-founded
the 2,500 member Churchill Club, a nonprofit business 
organization headquartered in Palo Alto.
<p>
Karlgaard graduated from Stanford in 1976.
<p>
He lives in Los Altos, California, with wife 
Marjorie and daughter Katherine.


</font>
