<title>William C. Myers </title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="ffffff">
<img src="discussi.gif">
<hr>
<blockquote>
<font face="arial">
<h2>William C. Myers </h2>

<p>

William C. Myers is Vice President for Policy and Senior Fellow at The
Progress & Freedom Foundation, a position he has held since December 1994.
 Mr. Myers directs the Foundation's projects and policy initiatives.

<p>
<img src="myers.gif" align=right hspace=5 vspace=5>
<p>

Mr. Myers has devoted his career to public policy research and strategic
analysis, focused primarily on U.S. domestic policy.  He has held senior
policy management positions with the American Legislative Exchange Council.
 He has served on the staff of the U.S. Senate Republican Policy Committee
and as a member of several state and federal advisory commissions including,
most recently, the Advisory Commission on Regulatory Barriers to Affordable
Housing at the U.S. Department of Housing and Urban Development.

<p>

Mr. Myers is a co-founder of the State Policy Network, an association of two
dozen state-based free market research groups; the creator and host of
StateLines, a weekly, televised public policy roundtable broadcast on NET;
and the founder of South Carolina's Opportunity Schools, a supplemental
educational program for low-income students, organized on the principle of
school choice.

<p>

Mr. Myers has written on a wide range of public policly issues.  His articles
and commentaries have appeared in more than 250 national and state
publications and on national and local television.  He has testified before
legislative committees in 22 states, and has delivered hundreds of policy
addresses before legislative, business, civic and public policy groups.

<p>

An alumnus of Yale University, Mr. Myers has completed graduate course work
at George Washington University and Georgetown University.  He is married to
Roberta Hood Myers and resides in Springfield, Virginia.
</font>
</body>
</html>

